m":"Birley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Grey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Gray  .","German: dialect variant of   Grau  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Ukrainian <b>Grushko</b>: nickname or topographic name derived from a Russian-influenced transliteration of <i>grushka</i> ‘pear, pear tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gray","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (especially Eastern Ulster; of Norman origin): habitational name from Graye in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Graec(i)us</i>, meaning ‘Greek’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. This is probably the chief source of the surname in Britain.","English: nickname for someone with gray hair or a gray beard, from Middle English <i>grey</i> (Old English <i>grǣg</i>, <i>grēg</i>) ‘gray’. In Ireland it has been used as a translation of various Gaelic surnames derived from <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled, gray’, including <b>Mac Giolla Riabhaigh</b>; see   McGreevy  . In North America, this surname has assimilated names with similar meaning from other languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."]},{"name":"Greiwe","meanings":["German: possibly a nickname from Middle High German <i>greibe</i> ‘sharp, tangy, dour’. Compare   Grey  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Grey was born in 1312, in Wilton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Henry DeGREY , 3rd Baron Grey de Wilton, was 30 and her mother, Anne Rockley, was 23. She had at least 1 son with Edward de Hillary. She died in 1359, in Birley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1312–1359":"1312–1359","1311–1370":"1311–1370","1320–1376":"1320–1376","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1354–1403":"1354–1403","1282–1342":"1282–1342","1290–1318":"1290–1318","1362":"1362","1282":"1282","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","1359":"1359","1403":"1403","1312":"1312","1311":"1311","1354":"1354","1376":"1376","10 Dec 1342":"10. detsember 1342","1342":"1342","1320":"1320","1319":"1319","1318":"1318","Wilton, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sandiacre, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wilton, Herefordshire, , England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Birley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Birley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1312–1359":"1312–1359","1311–1370":"1311–1370","1320–1376":"1320–1376","1319–1362":"1319–1362","1354–1403":"1354–1403","1282–1342":"1282–1342","1290–1318":"1290–1318","1362":"1362","1282":"1282","1370":"1370","1290":"1290","1359":"1359","1403":"1403","1312":"1312","1311":"1311","1354":"1354","1376":"1376","10 Dec 1342":"10. joulukuuta 1342","1342":"1342","1320":"1320","1319":"1319","1318":"1318","Wilton, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sandiacre, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskun